abstract: Over the past week, Democratic candidates have spent over $3.5 million in the four main TV markets in the state.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — It’s the final sprint in Iowa, but with three top candidates spending much of the past week in Washington as jurors for President Trump’s impeachment trial, televisions here in Iowa have been inundated with political ads to help provide air cover in this bifurcated political moment.
